cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on the security of diabetic data over the cloud and the communication channel between health care system components. It employs secure hash algorithm and secure socket shell to achieve reliability components of the proposed scheme. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper mentions storing patient records in the cloud using the Keil board that is connected to the infusion pump. This could potentially involve information retrieval techniques. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed system is based on the Internet of Things technology and employs IoT-cloud to monitor the diabetic patients. The Kiel board is embedded with Ethernet port and Cortex-M3 micro-controller that controls the insulin infusion pump. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper mentions implementing an easy way to control and monitor the diabetic insulin pump. This could involve software engineering techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a hardware implementation of a diabetic health care system using Alaris 8100 infusion pump and Keil LPC-1768 board. This could involve systems and control techniques.
